  strong Log Data

p
  | In the event of an app error, I collect diagnostic information through third-party services. This log data may
  | include your device’s Internet Protocol (IP) address, device name, operating system version, app configuration,
  | and the time and date of use.

p
  | Log data does not include workout content, encryption keys, or any end-to-end encrypted user data.

p
  strong Pro Version – AI Chat Planner

p
  | The Pro version of LiftLog includes an AI Chat Planner feature. When you use this feature, the messages you send
  | and relevant workout context you choose to include are transmitted to OpenAI to generate responses.

p
  | Data sent to the AI Chat Planner is not end-to-end encrypted, as it must be readable by OpenAI in order to
  | generate a response. No data is sent to OpenAI unless you actively use this feature.

p
  | OpenAI is not involved in any other aspect of LiftLog and does not receive access to your end-to-end encrypted
  | workout data outside of the AI Chat Planner feature.

